    <section id="notes" class="- topic/section " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/reference/r_operators.dita" xtrc="section:1;127:25">
      <title class="- topic/title " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/reference/r_operators.dita" xtrc="title:3;128:14">Notes</title>
      <ul class="- topic/ul " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/reference/r_operators.dita" xtrc="ul:1;129:11">
        <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/reference/r_operators.dita" xtrc="li:1;130:13">The <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/reference/r_operators.dita" xtrc="codeph:31;130:25">s</codeph> and <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/reference/r_operators.dita" xtrc="codeph:32;130:48">p&lt;N&gt;</codeph> operators
        require NLTK corpora. See
        <xref href="../../user-guide/tasks/t_download-nltk.dita" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/reference/r_operators.dita" xtrc="xref:1;132:66">Download NLTK language data</xref>.</li>
        <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/reference/r_operators.dita" xtrc="li:2;133:13">There is no negation operator. See the absence-check pattern in
        <xref href="../concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/reference/r_operators.dita" xtrc="xref:2;134:62">Rule design patterns</xref>.</li>
        <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/reference/r_operators.dita" xtrc="li:3;135:13">For multi-element XPath results with <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/reference/r_operators.dita" xtrc="codeph:33;135:58">==</codeph>, the
        evaluator requires every element to match. Target elements by position
        to avoid this. See
        <xref href="../concepts/c_known-limitations.dita" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/reference/r_operators.dita" xtrc="xref:3;138:59">Known limitations</xref>.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

